# This .dockerignore file is placed at the solution root. It helps to keep
# the Docker build context small and clean by excluding unnecessary files
# and directories, resulting in faster builds and smaller images.

## General Exclusions
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/out/
**/publish/

## IDE/Editor specific files
.vs/
.vscode/
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

## Git
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

## Documentation & CI
.github/
README.md

## Local Configuration
**/appsettings.Development.json
**/secrets.json
**/Properties/launchSettings.json

## Test Projects & Artifacts
Tests/
*.trx

## ML Model & Training
# The ML model is a build artifact. It's better to copy it into the image
# during a multi-stage build rather than including it in the initial context.
*.zip

## Node.js dependencies (if any, e.g., for Blazor client-side libraries)
**/node_modules/

## Other Project Sources
# When building a specific project (e.g., WebAPI), you don't need the source
# code of other runnable projects in the context. The Dockerfile will copy
# only what's needed.
FraudDetection.Dashboard/
FraudDetection.ML.Trainer/
FraudDetection.WebAPI/
FraudDetection.Worker/